The paper proposes a deep learning approach for the classification of seizures against non-seizures using an independently recurrent neural network (IndRNN). This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the extraction of temporal and spatial features, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of segment length on classification performance, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
